//   text-------------------

// assets:-  Contains static files such as images and global styles.
// components:-  Houses reusable UI components, further divided into common, layout, menu, order, and table-related components.
// contexts:- Manages global state using React Context API for authentication, menu data, and orders.
// hooks:- Contains custom hooks for accessing and manipulating state and data.
// pages:- Defines the structure and logic for different application pages.
// routes:- Configures navigation using React Router.
// services:- Handles API interactions and business logic, separating concerns for authentication, menu, and orders.
// utils:- Includes helper functions and constants.
// App.jsx:- The root component that renders the main application structure.
// index.js:- The entry point of the application.

